    <stitle>GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - INSTRUMENT CLUSTER</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTRUMENT CLUSTER</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x0803520">
            <title>Removing Instrument Cluster</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0803508">Figure 8</hotlnk>
                for the following:
            </para>
            <para>Remove the screw in each of the cluster corners and remove the cluster. The right gauge cluster
                contains the two mechanical air gauges. They have air line connections that must be removed for complete
                removal of the cluster.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove air from the vehicle primary and secondary systems.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The air gauges have connector-less push on fittings. To remove the line, depress the
                    blue collar and pull the line out. To install, just push the line into the blue collar.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connectors.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installing Instrument Cluster</title>
            <para>To install, reverse the process listed above.</para>
            <figure id="f0803508" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0803508" filename="../figg08/G0803508.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Left and Right Gauge Clusters</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
